column2: iMotions synchronization timestamp. Relative to data recording start
column3: Indicates which devices has a sample on the row
column9: Input source i.e. Mouse or API
column12: X-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column13: Y-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column14: X-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column15: Y-coordinate of the gaze point (2D) of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the computer screen)
column16: Pupil diameter of the left eye
column17: Pupil diameter of the right eye
column19: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the left eye
column20: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the right eye
column21: X-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column22: Y-coordinate of the left eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column23: X-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column24: Y-coordinate of the right eye (i.e. relative to the upper-left corner of the eye-tracker's capture box)
column25: Estimated distance between the gaze point (3D) and the gaze origin
column26: Up/down-rotation of the head. Positive when respondent is looking up. Negative when respondent is looking down.
column27: Left/right-rotation of the head. Positive when respondent is looking right. Negative when respondent is looking left.
column28: Tilt-rotation of the head. Positive when respondent is tilting to the left. Negative when respondent is tilting to the right.
column29: Estimated quality of the gaze direction measurement (considering the left eye individually)
column30: Estimated quality of the gaze direction measurement (considering the right eye individually)
column31: Distance between the lower and upper eyelid of the left eye
column32: Quality score reflecting the estimated accuracy of the eyelid measurement for the left eye
column33: Distance between the lower and upper eyelid of the right eye
column34: Quality score reflecting the estimated accuracy of the eyelid measurement for the right eye
column35: Quality score reflecting the estimated accuracy of the pupil size measurement for the left eye
column36: Quality score reflecting the estimated accuracy of the pupil size measurement for the right eye
column41: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column42: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen). Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column43: Gaze data X-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the X-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column44: Gaze data Y-coordinate (relative to top-left corner of the screen) with missing coordinates interpolated. Average of the Y-coordinates of the left and right eye.
column45: Estimated distance between the eye-tracker and the eyes, with missing values interpolated. Average of the eye tracker's distance to the left and right eye.
column46: Angular velocity of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how fast the eyes are moving at this point in time.
column47: Angular acceleration of the gaze at the current sample point, i.e. how much the eyes increased in speed at the current sample.
column48: Fixation number, counting from start of the recording.
column49: Fixation number, counting from start of the stimulus.
column50: X-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).
column51: Y-coordinate of the fixation centroid (relative to top-left corner of the screen).
column52: Start time of the fixation (relative to recording start).
column53: End time of the fixation (relative to recording start).
column55: Dispersion of the fixation, i.e. how much the fixation's gaze points are spread out.
column56: Saccade number, counting from start of the recording.
column57: Saccade number, counting from start of the stimulus.
column58: Start time of the saccade (relative to recording start).
column59: End time of the saccade (relative to recording start).
column61: Amplitude of the saccade, i.e. angular distance that the eyes travelled from start point to end point.
column62: Peak velocity of the saccade, i.e. the maximal speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column63: Peak acceleration of the saccade, i.e.  the maximal increase in speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column64: Peak deceleration of the saccade, i.e. the maximal decrease in speed of the eyes during this saccade.
column65: Direction of the saccade from its start point to end point, indicated as clockwise angles: 0 degrees mean a horizontal saccade from left to right, 90 degrees a vertical saccade from top to bottom.
